      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced garlic </strong>to the pan with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat, and add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> of the<strong> reserved starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Tip: Be careful when adding the water to the pan, it may splash!</p><p>Return the pan to the heat, sprinkle in your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and tear your <strong>parsley</strong> into the pan and stir it all together</p>",
